values: If you want access, please contact me via email or message me here if you have a LiveJournal account.

Due to the lack of the ability to block people from adding you as a friend here, I am going to take the unfortunate steps of making it Friends Only.

This is most unfortunate for my family members who view the site to see pictures of the kiddo, since that's all I ever put here.

If you are one of those people, let me know and we will figure out a way for you to have a login to see the pictures.

Long time no post. September was a busy month of vacation to Alabama. Yes, I took pictures, but it is such a gigantic tasks to post them here that I am going to only post a select few in the near future. For today, though, click on through to see a few from our walk in the park this morning. This is my good side.
This is my same good side. The other side is also good.
Mom's hand still seems to be bigger than mine.
This will be the quietest moment together all day, I can bet you that. I can barely sit still for more than ten seconds unless I'm reading a book of playing with toys. Outside I'm like a pinball on caffeine.
*ungh* And... HOVER!
This is just like flying! WHEE!
Rock rock rock rock rock.
I like coming to the park.

Close, close, closeup, Dad.
AIEEE! Mom is chasing! More! More!
So this is a cable car. Nice. Never understood the need for all those bulky doors.
Mom, I like you lots. You're awesome.
Argle Bargle finger in my snargle!

Well, folks, in one week we come to the end of year two of Miss MJW's adventures and we embark upon year three. I'm not sure how I will or should continue on. I enjoy doing these, but as she gets older she provides her own captions pretty much and mine are amusing but hers are much more astonishing. I am trying to figure out the 3rd year project for her. The first two years have been a blast, and we've still got a week to go with year two. :) AIEEE! This is too much fun! THE TICKLING!
Mom! Look! There's you with the camera in here! / DAD NOTE: As mom took the picture, Miss MJW pointed to the cat with a camera. FYI, this warming up with a blanket and hot tea is in August in San Francisco. Overcast, foggy, and mid 50s.
I saw this in a book! It's called 'downdog'! / DAD NOTE: This is actually true. She pulled down a yoga book, opened it to down dog and did the pose.
I'm learning how to be a lady with an umbrella. A poison tipped umbrella, yes, but even a lady has to protect herself.
Annnddd... off I go.

I am starting my day thoughtfully.
ah HA! I thought of something!
This is what I thought of! PLAYTIME WITH DAD!
WHEE! GALLOPING HORSIE!
Yey horsie! Hey, is it breezy in here or is it just me?
Awwww yeah! Rock climbing!
Ungh! This one's easy.
Totally easy. I'm up here. It's conquered.
I'll post for the camera on my conqueree.
This part here where my hands are, this was the most DANGEROUS part of the journey.
Now I am thinking about my next stage of conquering.
*hehehe* I think I know a good one.
I love these guys, and mom does too.
RUNNING! FLOWERS! ROCKS TO CLIMB!
Uhnf! Conquered another!
Whoa, this slide goes backwards!
C'mon slide! GO! Why am I not going backwards and up?
Fine. I think my work here is done.
Bigger game to tackle! Rope bridge!
I think I'm doing pretty good for a kid that isn't even two years old yet. TAKE THAT BIG KIDS!

*heh heh* I got up here and the rock tickles!
Gentle. I'm good at being gentle.
Serious Mila is serious.
Wow. Yellow flowers are lovely!
THIS FLOWER IS HUGE! ... HUGE!
Huge, but yes, delicate.

Here are just a few pictures from the recent trip to Alabama. Water, water everywhere...
...that mom and dad won't let me drink.
Gigi telling me that she'll let me drink pool water whenever I want.
SO... TEMPTING!
Wait, I've been told water from the hose is ok to drink as long as I don't stick the hose in my mouth.
Dad and I accessorizing.
HA! This water is so fun there's no need to even TRY to drink it!
Ka-chow! Caught ya!
See! The hose is nowhere near my mouth! This was, I was told, the acceptable method.
I expect praise for my startling ability to follow these ridiculously complicated rules about drinking water.
My cousin shows me how to create stacks and explains the difference between black and yellow.
Yet again, pool time.
Man, this pool is huge. There's no way I can drink all this pool water.
*hehehehe* I like mom. She's funny.
I love mom a lot too.

First off I want to apologize for so few updates here. I have taken a lot of pictures and what happens is that I post them to Facebook and then so many get piled up I don't post them here. I am doing a minor catchup here tonight, though, but I am rinsing out the difference and going with some of the most recent best shots I love. *heh heh* It tickles.
Profile shot. Thanks dad.
SNEAKY! I SEE YOU!
Awesome! Color contrast is fun!

*touch* Let's see if I can tickle the grasses.
I am pondering the grasses of California.
Mom is definitely someone I love and whom gets a hug.
*heh* This is the most awesome morning in a while.
I love mom and I love this tree.

Not in order either. Oh well.

Whoa.

SOCCER BALL!

From Jenn in IM today: "You really need to make sure that you lock the cabinet back at night. I was cleaning up a really messy sticky poop and came back into the room to find everything she could lift out of the cabinet and she was trying to free Tom Servo from captivity."

WOO! OUTSIDE! [Dad Note: Someone has had a cold and not been outside much.]

*hehehehehehe* Dirt. If I can get it on my face with the snot, it's totally going home with me.
*squeeze* Not compressible, but nevertheless AWESOME. Mom, did know that dirt flows like water right out of your hands?
*stretch* Look, being a kid takes a lot of flexibility.

"Yes. Dirt is great. Go, kid, go."

This is a little experiment for linking/embedding pictures from the Facebook galleries. Let me know if you can see them or not. No captions today. I'm at work and just throwing these up.

Hey! It's a ball. In a puddle. You've told me in the past to not go into puddles. Is this a trick?
Ok. I have the ball, but I'm still trying to figure out if I can get in the puddle or not.
*contemplating*
The answer seems to be yes!
This is awesome.
No WONDER I've been wanting to get in puddles! Look at this!
Although, this sand is a little weird.
*splash splash splash* Just like bath time!
Muahahahaha!
Dang. This sand is stubborn.
Wow. I still can't believe I got to actually dig around in a puddle. They even brought some of my favorite stuff from the house!
Alright. Time to dig my way out of here. *umph*
Gee, Mom, I think you're enjoying the swing more than I am.
WHEE! I'M GOING UP!
WAY UP! MOMMM! YOU'RE NOT LOOKING!
Fine. Two can play that "I'm not looking." game.
*heh* Just kidding, Mom. This is fun. But I'm sleepy. Let's go home.

This is my kingdom; my domain; my land of conquer.

Caution: Mila At ***.
Again. (DAD COMMENTARY: This is her sign language for 'again' and it is the ASL one. She uses it for a lot of things. This 'again' was for us to chase her.)

...hahahahahah... AIIEEE! I'M BEING GOTTEN!
Ok, all finished with the chase. Stupid old parents! I could chase for HOURS but they only last a few minutes.
Whoa. Did I just go into another dimension?
*slurp slurp* Yum.
This is good stuff.
Chewing on park benches is a form of meditation.
I'm trying to talk dad into trying it. He needs to relax a little and open his mind.

*splash splash splash*

What a lovely day to walk in the grass.
I wonder if there are any challenging stairs in my future.
The bridge! In the Tarot is means overcoming obstacles. I'm damn good at that, though, so maybe this is my mascot.
I mean, look at me navigating this bridge. It's like nobody's business!
They should just put a picture of ME on the Tarot for overcoming obstacles. Bridge, schmidge!

I have recently been considering abandoning LiveJournal altogether.  More and more I am inclined to slowly pull further back from a public persona.

Friends Only is an option, but I truly need feedback from those of you willing to be logged in to see pictures of Mila.

I am considering other options and I welcome ideas.  I have even thought of resorting to simply posting the photos on Picasa and emailing those that are interested when those photos go up.

Suggestions?
